summary: In this context, methylsulfanylmethane and dimethyl sulfide are both volatile organic compounds (VOCs) being investigated for their catalytic conversion performance using a specific catalyst, MnO/Fe2O3. The experiments focus on the effects of these compounds on catalyst performance, particularly regarding sulfur-poisoning effects. While both compounds are related as VOCs in the study, the specific interactions or differences between them are not elaborated upon in detail.
